@page "/about"

<script src="/js/rateLimiter.js"></script>
<script>rateLimitPageLoads(15, 60000, 'aboutpage:loads');</script>

<head>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com/" crossorigin="" />
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    as="style"
    onload="this.rel='stylesheet'"
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?display=swap&amp;family=Noto+Sans%3Awght%40400%3B500%3B700%3B900&amp;family=Space+Grotesk%3Awght%40400%3B500%3B700"
  />

  <title>Stitch Design</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="data:image/x-icon;base64," />
  <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com?plugins=forms,container-queries"></script>
</head>

<body
  class="bg-[var(--background-dark)] text-[var(--text-primary)]"
  style='font-family: "Space Grotesk", "Noto Sans", sans-serif;'
>
  <div class="relative flex min-h-screen flex-col overflow-x-hidden">
    <div class="layout-container flex h-full grow flex-col">
      <div class="px-10 md:px-40 flex flex-1 justify-center py-5">
        <div class="layout-content-container flex flex-col max-w-[960px] flex-1">

          <!-- Card Container -->
          <div class="bg-card p-6 mb-6 relative">

            <!-- Title -->
            <p class="text-white tracking-light text-[32px] font-bold leading-tight mb-3">
              Message from the Author
            </p>

            <!-- Author Image -->
            <img
              src="/Images/Author.png"
              class="w-40 h-40 rounded-full object-cover border border-[#262626] shadow-lg float-right ml-10 -mt-4 mb-4"
            />

            <!-- Text Content -->
            <div class="text-white text-base font-normal leading-normal text-justify">
              <p class="mb-3">
                <strong>Hello 👋 and thank you for visiting my website!</strong>
              </p>

              <p class="mb-3">
                I truly enjoyed creating this project and I hope you’ve enjoyed exploring it
                as much as I enjoyed building it. The idea of making a website like this came
                to me long before I even started coding it, which is why it feels so special to me now.
              </p>

              <p class="mb-3">
                My name is <strong>Diana (Di for friends)</strong>, and I’m from Ukraine.
                I’ve been working with <i>C#</i> for over 4 years, and I’ve realized that
                building digital experiences like this is something I deeply enjoy. I like to
                think of myself as an artist — my laptop is the brush, and this website is my masterpiece.
              </p>

              <p class="mb-3">
                When you first arrive, you’re welcomed by the <i>Home Page</i>, where you can
                navigate to the <i>Strategy Prediction</i> tool for custom stints. Next, you
                can visit the <i>Next Grand Prix Page</i>, which features useful information
                about the upcoming race — from circuit details to Grand Prix insights,
                beautifully decorated with images provided by the <i>Pexels API</i>, and
                weather data powered by the <i>api.open-meteo.com</i>.
              </p>

              <p class="mb-3">
                But the highlight is the <strong><i>Race Strategy Page</i></strong> — my favorite
                part of the site. Here you can choose any Grand Prix, click <strong>View Analysis</strong>,
                and dive into a detailed <i>Race Strategy Analysis</i>. You’ll find visualizations
                of plausible driver stints, a tire compound key, and last year’s race statistics.
              </p>

              <p class="mb-3">
                And now, you’re here — reading this message. <strong>Thank you for being part
                of the journey 💙💛</strong>
              </p>

              <p class="mb-3">
                But this isn’t just about me — it’s about building a community. If you have
                cool ideas, improvements, suggestions, or want to collaborate, I’d love to hear from you!
              </p>

              <p class="mb-3">
                📩 Email:
                <a class="text-[var(--primary-color)] font-bold" href="mailto:antoniukdin@gmail.com">
                  antoniukdin@gmail.com
                </a>
              </p>

              <p class="mb-3">
                🔗 LinkedIn:
                <a
                  class="text-[var(--primary-color)] font-bold"
                  href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/d%D1%96ana-antoniuk-067b28362/"
                >
                  Diana Antoniuk
                </a>
              </p>

              <p class="mb-3">
                <strong>P.S.</strong> A huge thank you for the help and emotional support from
                my friends and family — especially Losiash, Hvostyk, My Mother, Sonia, and Elia.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- End Card Container -->

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style type="text/tailwindcss">
    :root {
      --primary-color: #EF4444;
      --background-dark: #0A0A0A;
      --background-light: #141414;
      --border-color: #262626;
      --text-primary: #E5E7EB;
      --text-secondary: #888888;
    }

    body {
      font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      background-color: var(--background-dark);
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    .bg-card {
      background-color: var(--background-light);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      box-shadow: 0 10px 15px -3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1),
                  0 4px 6px -4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    .bg-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-4px);
    }
  </style>
</body>
